        <h2>Our Best Services</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Cancer Screening & Early Detection</strong><br>
                Screening programs aim to detect cancer before symptoms appear, using tests like mammograms,
                Pap smears, colonoscopies, and low-dose CT scans. Early detection improves survival rates and
                can reduce the need for aggressive treatment.
            </li>

            <li>
                <strong>Diagnosis & Imaging</strong><br>
                Once cancer is suspected, imaging tests such as X-rays, CT scans, MRIs, and PET scans are used
                to locate tumors and assess spread. A biopsy is then performed to examine cells under a
                microscope, confirming cancer type and stage.
            </li>

            <li>
                <strong>Cancer Treatment</strong><br>
                Treatment depends on cancer type and stage, and may include surgery to remove tumors,
                chemotherapy to kill cancer cells, radiation to target localized areas, and newer approaches
                like immunotherapy and targeted therapy.
            </li>

            <li>
                <strong>Supportive & Palliative Care</strong><br>
                This care focuses on improving quality of life by managing symptoms and treatment side effects
                such as pain, nausea, and fatigue. Palliative care can be provided alongside curative
                treatment to support both physical and emotional well-being.
            </li>

            <li>
                <strong>Follow-Up / Survivorship Care</strong><br>
                After treatment ends, regular check-ups monitor for recurrence and manage long-term side
                effects. Survivorship care may include lifestyle counseling, rehabilitation, and psychological
                support to promote long-term health.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>
